OL,7,FThe minister said he was party to
OL,8,Fconversations about the allegations
OL,9,Fwhile training to be a member of the
OL,10,Fspecial forces, but said he considered
OL,11,Fthem at the time to be "rumours".
OL,13,FMr Mercer also told the inquiry
OL,14,Fanother friend of his said he had been
OL,15,Fasked to carry a "dropped weapon" -
OL,16,Fwhich is weapon that could be used to
OL,17,Fput next to the body of an unarmed
OL,18,FAfghan to make it look as if they had
OL,19,Fbeen armed when they were killed.
